<div class="dummy-body select">
  <div class="section-header">frost-select</div>
  {{frost-select
    data=longdata
    hook='mySelect'
  }}
  <p>In order to use this component you must provide an outlet for it to render the dropdown in like so:</p>

  <div class="snippet">
    {{format-markdown "```handlebars
{{frost-select-outlet
  hook='selectOutlet'
}}
```"}}
  </div>

  <p>In the event you want to render different selects in different outlets you may also used named outlets like so:</p>

  <div class="snippet">
    {{format-markdown "```handlebars
{{frost-select-outlet
  hook='namedSelectOutlet'
  name='foo-bar'
}}
…
{{frost-select
  hook='mySelect'
  renderTarget='foo-bar'
  …
}}
```"}}
  </div>

  <div class="section-title">Content</div>
  <hr>
  <div class="section">

    <div class="example">
      <div class="title">data</div>
      <div class="demo">
        {{frost-select
          data=data
          hook='mySelect'
        }}
      </div>
      <div class="snippet">
        {{format-markdown "```handlebars
{{frost-select
  data=data
  hook='mySelect'
}}
```"}}
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="example">
      <div class="title">clearing</div>
      <i>works by setting the property being passed as 'selectedValue' to an empty string<br/></i>
      <div class="demo">
        {{log preSelectedValueForClearing}}
        {{frost-select
          data=data
          hook='mySelect'
          selectedValue=preSelectedValueForClearing
          onChange=(action 'onChangeClearable')
        }}
        {{frost-button text='Clear'
          hook='clearButton'
          onClick=(action 'onClearSelect')
          priority='secondary'
          size='small'
          text='Clear'
        }}
      </div>
      <div class="snippet">
        {{format-markdown "```handlebars
{{frost-select
  data=data
  hook='mySelect'
  selectedValue=preSelectedValueForClearing
}}
```"}}
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>

